@node Bugs "Bugs"
Bugs -

	None left that I know of.
@endnode

@node ToDo "To Do"
To Do -

	· Allow @{i}AmiPOP@{ui} to get signals while it's transfering.  Currently it can't
	be hidden/quit while a transfer is in progress.  This is lame.
@endnode

@node NotifyNote "A Note about Notify"
	The current implmentation of the "Notify" feature is done in such a way that the
	program is easy to maintain, and remains very small.  I have had a LARGE number of
	requests to make the requester that "Notify" brings up be done in such a way that
	it will timeout, or will continue transfering files, even if the requester is not
	satisfied.  I have looked into this prospect, and have concluded that it would
	make the code more cumbersome, and larger than need be.  If users with to have a
	reliable method of being notified when new mail arrives, I urge them to take a look
	at another program I wrote, which IMHO complements AmiPOP quite nicely.  It is
	called "Sabot", and can do just about anything you want when new mail arrives.
	"Sabot" is mostl likely available from the location you received AmiPOP from.  If not
	please contact me, and I will be happy to provide you with a copy of "Sabot".
@endnode

